<br>
I can really get into the multiplayer side of the game though.  Easily the new battle net interface and ladder is a lot better done than in Starcraft.  Finding a ladder game or a non competitive game is a breeze.  Though the quality of play isn't really that great yet since the game is so new.<br>
<br>
The actual gameplay is a lot different than in Starcraft.  War3 focuses more on smaller armies.  The units have a lot more HPS so you're able to focus more attention to the battles.  War3 adds a new twist to the genre too with heros.  They're basically beefed up units that can gain exp and new abilities.  A well used hero ability can easily turn the tide of a battle.<br>
<br>
The new features added isn't for everyone though, gameplay is less focused on economy and massing and more focused on unit selection and how you control them during battle.<br>
<br>
Personally I like it so far, I played the early beta builds and didn't care for it much.  But retail is really enjoyable. <p><center>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105067"><img src="http://sairah.homestead.com/files/ElloneSig.jpg" ALT="Push my buttons"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uskydarkener.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skydarkener</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wanderer</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/6/02 10:58:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2738.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://outside.clanpages.com/wisp.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warcraft III revues</span><hr size=1> It's my opinion that Blizzard cant make a bad game.  Theirs are the most eagerly anticipated of the genre for a reason, and I dont regret standing in line at midnight on July 2nd to get my copy, or paying 90 bucks US for the Collecters Edition.<br>
<br>
I am nearing completion of the second campaign, which is Undead (the first is humans), and have enjoyed the storyline immensely (though I doubt you will if you like the human faction).  The game is definately more oriented towards smaller battles, with most of the missions being completed with about two &quot;squads&quot; (blocks of 12) of troops led by a hero or two.<br>
<br>
Heroes are a sight to behold.  As Sairah said, they are basically special characters that lead forces and have special abilities.  They can go up in level, gain more abilities, and their hp and mana increase too.  Not only are they a great boon for your forces, but a serious threat when used against you.  I've lost games because of the human Archmagi, who's area effect spell is devestating.<br>
<br>
Something that is different for Blizzard is the army balancing.  No longer are there 2 or 3 armies, each with the same units, only with different faces and names.  Each army has its own strengths and weaknesses, and while there are similar units in each army, no two are exactly alike.  For example, each army has its own &quot;elite&quot; foot troop unit, the Human Knight, the Undead Abomination (many corpses sewn together), the Orc Tauren (minotaurs), and the Night Elf's Druid of the Claw, but each unit is not the same.  Their damage types and amounts differ (some have more than one option), as do their armor ratings, and hit points.<br>
<br>
Overall, the armies each have their own feel.  I've yet to play orcs, but the humans are very defensive, and the undead seem to be all-rounders.  The night elves (who are actually more like wood elves) are very stealth oriented, and by far my favorite so far.  They actually benefit from waiting for nightfall before scouting or launching an attack.  Oh yeah, did I mention the game has day and night, and there are ramifications to each side?<br>
<br>
Heh, enough with my rambling.  Bottom line is that its a great game, and well worth the 60 bucks.  If you can afford it, get the collecters edition for 20 more. <p><B>Shas'O-Jefe'mit-Vior'la</B><BR><I>The Skydarkener</I><BR>Commander of the Vior'Eht - <B>Purebloods</B><BR><I>Untainted.<BR>Unstoppable</I><BR><BR><A HREF="http://pub43.ezboard.com/btauva">For the Greater Good</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upopitinythug.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Popi Tinythug</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/6/02 11:31:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2738.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.fortunecity.com/popidathug/poppic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warcraft III revues</span><hr size=1> I played beta for a week or two. Its really too slow and theres too much crap to learn, spells, items etc... <br>
